        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(config): write local editor schema",
        "body": "I don’t seem to be able to touch my `openclaw.json` without breaking something, and it’s hard to discover all the available options. This PR adds a small breadcrumb for humans and our agents: when OpenClaw writes config, it also leaves behind the local schema editors need for validation and IntelliSense.\n\n## What changed\n\n- Writes or refreshes `openclaw.schema.json` next to the active `openclaw.json` after OpenClaw-owned config writes.\n- Adds `\"$schema\": \"./openclaw.schema.json\"` only when the root config file is already being committed and no non-empty schema is present.\n- Keeps existing non-empty `$schema` values alone.\n- Respects explicit `$schema` removal; `openclaw config unset '$schema'` does not immediately add it back.\n- Keeps include-backed writes root-preserving: the included fragment is updated, the schema sidecar is refreshed best-effort, and the root config is not rewritten just to add `$schema`.\n- Reuses the same schema helper for `openclaw config schema` and the editor-facing schema file.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: OpenClaw-owned config writes create a local editor schema, add a root `$schema` reference when the root file is naturally rewritten, preserve include-backed roots, and do not let editor-schema side effects break the requested config write.\n- Real environment tested: local OpenClaw source checkout on Linux, with isolated temporary `HOME` / `OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH` values so this did not touch my real `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`.\n- Exact steps or command run after this patch:\n\n```bash\ntmp_home=$(mktemp -d)\nmkdir -p \"$tmp_home/.openclaw\"\nconfig=\"$tmp_home/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"\nprintf '{\"gateway\":{\"mode\":\"local\"}}\\n' > \"$config\"\nHOME=\"$tmp_home\" OPENCLAW_CONFIG_PATH=\"$config\" OPENCLAW_TEST_FAST=1 \\\n  node scripts/run-node.mjs config set gateway.port 18790 --strict-json\n```\n\n- Evidence after fix: terminal output from the isolated runtime write showed that the config was updated, a local schema reference was present, and the schema sidecar existed with expected root fields:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"schemaRef\": \"./openclaw.schema.json\",\n  \"port\": 18790,\n  \"schemaFileExists\": true,\n  \"hasGateway\": true,\n  \"hasChannels\": true,\n  \"hasSchemaProperty\": { \"type\": \"string\" }\n}\n```\n\nVS Code also picks up the local schema and shows IntelliSense:\n\n<img width=\"600\" height=\"320\" alt=\"VS Code IntelliSense for openclaw.json using the local OpenClaw schema\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/6b1c64e9-021a-4e2f-b13f-f7af21400c33\" />\n\n- Observed result after fix: `openclaw.json` was updated with the requested config value and `\"$schema\": \"./openclaw.schema.json\"`, and `openclaw.schema.json` existed beside it with expected root schema fields. The follow-up code cleanup keeps include-backed writes root-preserving while still refreshing the sidecar best-effort.\n- What was not tested: Nix-managed config writes, because that path is intentionally immutable and config writers refuse Nix-mode writes.\n\n## Include-backed compatibility proof\n\nFinal contract after the holistic cleanup:\n\n- Include-backed single-top-level writes update the include target only.\n- The root config remains byte-for-byte unchanged; this avoids raw JSON5 root surgery and preserves comments/formatting.\n- `openclaw.schema.json` is still refreshed best-effort beside the root config.\n- If sidecar generation fails, the requested include-backed write still succeeds.\n\nRegression coverage:\n\n- `src/config/mutate.test.ts`: proves an include-backed `plugins.json5` write refreshes the editor schema without rewriting the root config.\n- `src/config/mutate.test.ts`: simulates an `EACCES` editor-schema failure and proves the include-backed write still commits while the root remains unchanged.\n- `src/config/io.write-config.test.ts`: simulates an `EACCES` sidecar write failure and proves the primary `openclaw.json` write still persists.\n\n## Explicit unset proof\n\nContract:\n\n- Ordinary missing or blank root `$schema` values are stamped when the root config is being committed.\n- If a config write explicitly includes `unsetPaths: [[\"$schema\"]]`, the writer does not add `$schema` back.\n\nRegression coverage:\n\n- `src/config/io.write-config.test.ts`: writes a config with `$schema`, performs a write with `unsetPaths: [[\"$schema\"]]`, and verifies the persisted `openclaw.json` no longer has `$schema`.\n\n## Tested\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/config/io.write-config.test.ts src/config/mutate.test.ts src/cli/config-cli.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor-heartbeat-template-repair.test.ts src/agents/workspace-templates.test.ts src/agents/tools/pdf-tool.model-config.test.ts\ncorepack pnpm exec oxlint src/config/editor-schema.ts src/config/io.ts src/config/io.write-prepare.ts src/config/mutate.ts src/config/io.write-config.test.ts src/config/mutate.test.ts src/commands/doctor-heartbeat-template-repair.test.ts\nnode --import tsx scripts/generate-base-config-schema.ts --check\ncorepack pnpm config:schema:check\ngit diff --check\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Nix-managed config is still intentionally immutable; this does not change that path.\n- Manual edits do not refresh the schema by themselves. The schema is refreshed when OpenClaw owns the config write.\n- The main review question is now just product/compatibility acceptance of the local schema sidecar and root `$schema` on root-owned writes.",
